	<section class="section" id="faq">
				<div class="container">
					<div class="sec-header" style="text-align:center;">
						<span class="eyebrow">FAQ</span>
						<h2 class="sec-head">Straight answers first.</h2>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-list">
						<div class="faq-item open">
							<button class="faq-q"
								><span
									>How much does a roof replacement cost in
									New Hampshire?</span
								><span class="plus"></span></button
							>
							<div class="faq-a">
								<p>
									Most full roof replacements in New Hampshire
									run between $8,000 and $22,000, depending on
									roof size, pitch, material, and how much of
									the underlying deck needs repair. We provide
									a free, itemized estimate after an on-site
									inspection so you know the exact cost before
									any work begins.
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="faq-item">
							<button class="faq-q"
								><span
									>Will my homeowners insurance cover storm or
									wind damage?</span
								><span class="plus"></span></button
							>
							<div class="faq-a">
								<p>
									Most NH homeowners policies cover sudden
									storm, wind, and hail damage, though
									coverage details vary by carrier. We
									document the damage, meet with your
									adjuster, and help you understand what your
									policy covers as part of every storm damage
									claim.
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="faq-item">
							<button class="faq-q"
								><span
									>How long does a typical roof replacement
									take?</span
								><span class="plus"></span></button
							>
							<div class="faq-a">
								<p>
									Most residential roof replacements are
									completed in one to three days, weather
									permitting. Larger or steeper roofs, and
									commercial flat roofs, can take longer.
									You'll get a specific timeline in your
									written estimate.
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="faq-item">
							<button class="faq-q"
								><span>Do you offer emergency roof repair?</span
								><span class="plus"></span></button
							>
							<div class="faq-a">
								<p>
									Yes. We offer 24/7 emergency response for
									active leaks, storm damage, and structural
									concerns anywhere in our New Hampshire
									service area, with temporary tarping
									available the same day.
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="faq-item">
							<button class="faq-q"
								><span
									>Do you work on commercial and flat roofs?</span
								><span class="plus"></span></button
							>
							<div class="faq-a">
								<p>
									Yes. We install and repair commercial
									low-slope and flat roofing systems for
									retail, office, and multi-unit properties,
									in addition to residential pitched roofs.
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>